This adds statements like `lemma Ici_of_Real {x : ‚Ñù} : Real.toEReal '' Set.Ici x = Set.Ico ‚Üëx ‚ä§` for the eight kinds of intervals (plus versions of `exists_between` when one endpoint is a real number).

See [here](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/sInf.20.28Real.2EtoEReal.20'.20'.20.2E.2E.2E.29/near/410765558) on Zulip.

Why not this instead of these 2 lemmas?
```
lemma exists_between_ofReal {x z : EReal} (h : x < z) : ‚àÉ y : ‚Ñù, x < y ‚àß y < z := by
```
Because I want one of the inequalities to be between reals and not reals coerced to `EReal`s.
But it certainly makes sense to add your version, too.
Your two lemmas are both an `EReal.coe_lt_coe_iff` rewrite away from Yury's lemma. That seems better to me.
These should be `@[simp]`. BTW, do we have `Set.preimage` lemmas? If no, then please add them too.

```suggestion
lemma image_toEReal_Icc {x y : ‚Ñù} : Real.toEReal '' Set.Icc x y = Set.Icc ‚Üëx ‚Üëy := by
```
You mean like `Real.toEReal ‚Åª¬π' Set.Ixy ... = ...` ? I don't think so.

```suggestion
lemma image_coe_Icc {x y : ‚Ñù} : Real.toEReal '' Set.Icc x y = Set.Icc ‚Üëx ‚Üëy := by
```
is the name I would guess for this lemma

OK; I'll change the names.
Regarding preimage lemmas, I think there will be 24 cases (for I{c|o}{c|o} one has to distinguish cases according to whether the left end is bot or not/the right end is top or not --> 4*4 cases, and for I{c|o}i whether the left end is bot or not --> 2*2 cases, similarly for Ii{c|o} --> 2*2 cases). I'll add them unless somebody objects.
I think they all make sense to have.

```suggestion
lemma preimage_coe_Icc (x y : ‚Ñù) : Real.toEReal ‚Åª¬π' Icc x y = Icc x y := by
```
and all similar lemmas since they are rewriting lemmas.
The simp nf linter is right here. You should not have this lemma (as in, it's not even worth having as a non-simp lemma. Same for the other few that were tagged.
The proof should be quicker if you use the fact that `Icc a b = Ici a inter Iic b`
OK, simplified the proofs.
Same here. Arguing with intersections should be shorter, although you will need to use the fact that the coercion is injective.
This does not work; you end up with `Ico ‚Üëx ‚ä§ ‚à© Ioc ‚ä• ‚Üëy = Ici ‚Üëx ‚à© Iic ‚Üëy`, but `Ioc ‚ä• ‚Üëy = Iic ‚Üëy` (say) is false, so the equality of intersections is non-trivial.
(Of course, one *can* prove the equality of the intersections, but then the proof is no longer simpler...)
Ah yeah sorry, that's because you have more elements in the codomain.

```suggestion
lemma exists_between_coe {x z : EReal} (h : x < z) : ‚àÉ y : ‚Ñù, x < y ‚àß y < z := by
```
or
```suggestion
lemma exists_between_coe_real {x z : EReal} (h : x < z) : ‚àÉ y : ‚Ñù, x < y ‚àß y < z := by
```
since the function is called `Real.toEReal`, not `EReal.ofReal`.
Do you need the arrows here?
Yes, otherwise I get a "type mismatch" complaint.
Oh okay interesting

and all the ones below
